ks-or-publishing-shouldnt-be-all-about-quantity/">There Are Too Many Books; Or, Publishing Shouldn’t Be All About Quantity</a></strong><span class="post_attribute center">April 11, 2024 by <a href="https://lithub.com/author/mariskreizman/">Maris Kreizman</a><div class="post_comment_count"><a href="https://lithub.com/there-are-too-many-books-or-publishing-shouldnt-be-all-about-quantity/" title="There Are Too Many Books; Or, Publishing Shouldn’t Be All About Quantity"><i class="fa fa-comments-o"></i>6</a></div></span></li><li><div class="post_circle_thumb"><div class="article_num">4.</div><a href="https://lithub.com/the-ten-cringiest-things-in-poetry/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/moon-150x150.jpg" alt="" /></a></div><strong class="title"><a href="https://lithub.com/the-ten-cringiest-things-in-poetry/">The ten cringiest things in poetry.</a></strong><span class="post_attribute center">April 8, 2024 by <a href="https://lithub.com/author/jessiegaynor/">Jessie Gaynor</a><div class="post_comment_count"><a href="https://lithub.com/the-ten-cringiest-things-in-poetry/" title="The ten cringiest things in poetry."><i class="fa fa-comments-o"></i>0</a></div></span></li></ul></li>
